1
00:00:35,920 --> 00:00:37,240
Two years passed peacefully

2
00:00:38,600 --> 00:00:39,759
I almost forgot

3
00:00:41,039 --> 00:00:41,479
that I

4
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:44,200
am going to die

5
00:00:47,159 --> 00:00:47,840
It's been two years

6
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:49,359
and I still can't

7
00:00:49,359 --> 00:00:51,200
face death calmly

8
00:00:55,240 --> 00:00:56,560
Wildflowers gradually withering

9
00:01:00,759 --> 00:01:01,840
Decaying fallen leaves

10
00:01:08,879 --> 00:01:10,079
Kittens born to stray cats

11
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,480
Empty bottles after finishing drinks

12
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:18,439
all constantly remind me that time is limited

13
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:20,319
Death

14
00:01:21,439 --> 00:01:22,400
follows me like a shadow

15
00:01:37,519 --> 00:01:37,959
Darn it

16
00:01:43,079 --> 00:01:44,680
You're so close with A Fu now

17
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:45,560
ask him for me

18
00:01:45,560 --> 00:01:46,760
how much longer I have to live

19
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:48,120
The students are waiting for me

20
00:01:48,560 --> 00:01:49,079
Okay, okay

21
00:01:49,079 --> 00:01:49,680
Then... then you...

22
00:01:49,920 --> 00:01:52,000
at least ask him how I'll die, okay?

23
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:53,560
Will it be an accident or an illness?

24
00:01:53,560 --> 00:01:54,840
Will it hurt? I'm mentally prepared

25
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,599
I'm afraid of pain

26
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,920
It's not like I haven't asked

27
00:01:57,519 --> 00:01:59,280
Come on, you've been anxious for two years

28
00:01:59,480 --> 00:02:01,040
I'm actually glad their lips are sealed

29
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:01,959
and they didn't tell you

30
00:02:02,159 --> 00:02:03,359
If you actually found out

31
00:02:03,959 --> 00:02:05,439
imagine how bandaged your hands would be

32
00:02:05,439 --> 00:02:07,599
It hurts, hurts! Scared! Scared of pain!

33
00:02:08,039 --> 00:02:09,159
It hurts, it hurts

34
00:02:09,680 --> 00:02:10,800
Ever since Xu Rui became

35
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:12,680
a potential client for Life Energy Exchange

36
00:02:12,840 --> 00:02:14,719
she has A Fu wrapped around her finger

37
00:02:15,080 --> 00:02:16,240
Xu Rui's intelligence and wit

38
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:17,960
completely impressed the alien

39
00:02:18,240 --> 00:02:19,719
Not only is A Fu at her beck and call

40
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,560
he even wants to invite her as a special consultant

41
00:02:21,840 --> 00:02:23,680
Let me tell you the holidays first

42
00:02:24,439 --> 00:02:26,360
Spring Festival, New Year's Day

43
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:28,560
Labor Day, Dragon Boat Festival, Mid-Autumn Festival

44
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,240
Birthdays, National Day

45
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:32,479
Double 11, Double 12

46
00:02:32,960 --> 00:02:33,840
Double 12

47
00:02:34,439 --> 00:02:36,520
Birthdays are half price

48
00:02:36,759 --> 00:02:37,159
Half price

49
00:02:37,319 --> 00:02:38,960
Double 11 is 110 percent

50
00:02:39,039 --> 00:02:39,560
110 percent

51
00:02:40,479 --> 00:02:42,240
Ten... ten... isn't 110 percent more expensive?

52
00:02:43,680 --> 00:02:44,520
1.1 percent

53
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:47,240
Double 12 is 1.2 percent

54
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,439
And for other holidays

55
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,639
everything is half price

56
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,199
Everything is half price

57
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,639
Did you get that?

58
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,599
So that's how it works

59
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:54,639
Got it, got it

60
00:02:54,919 --> 00:02:56,479
As for my mom

61
00:03:02,719 --> 00:03:04,039
What are you two doing?

62
00:03:06,319 --> 00:03:08,039
Fang'er, why are you waking up just now?

63
00:03:08,039 --> 00:03:09,000
Look what time it is

64
00:03:09,639 --> 00:03:11,159
The breakfast I brought you is cold

65
00:03:11,479 --> 00:03:12,039
Xiaoyin

66
00:03:12,479 --> 00:03:13,879
Let me have a sip of your coffee

67
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,280
This is an Iced Americano

68
00:03:15,919 --> 00:03:17,080
Can you drink it on an empty stomach?

69
00:03:17,319 --> 00:03:17,919
No problem

70
00:03:19,879 --> 00:03:20,520
Fang'er

71
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:23,280
You don't act like a mom at all anymore

72
00:03:25,639 --> 00:03:26,599
Where are you two going?

73
00:03:26,639 --> 00:03:28,719
Xi and I need to rent a small warehouse for our online shop

74
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,319
We can't keep piling stuff in the dorm

75
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:32,159
The owner is only free in the morning

76
00:03:32,240 --> 00:03:33,319
Where is the warehouse?

77
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:33,919
Seagull Street

78
00:03:34,439 --> 00:03:35,479
That's a bit far

79
00:03:35,599 --> 00:03:37,639
There's Professor Wang Mei's class at ten o'clock

80
00:03:37,639 --> 00:03:38,439
Can you make it back in time?

81
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:40,560
It's fine, the teachers will understand

82
00:03:40,840 --> 00:03:42,360
Teachers can't stop us

83
00:03:42,360 --> 00:03:43,319
from finding our own path

84
00:03:46,400 --> 00:03:47,039
Where's Zhuyun?

85
00:03:48,520 --> 00:03:50,319
Last night she said that for her grad school English exam

86
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:51,879
she got several cloze test questions wrong

87
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:53,520
She was depressed all night

88
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:54,479
Her boyfriend said

89
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:55,080
"It's okay"

90
00:03:55,360 --> 00:03:56,360
"If you don't pass, let's not take it"

91
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:56,919
"I'll support you"

92
00:03:57,080 --> 00:03:57,599
And then?

93
00:03:57,680 --> 00:04:00,120
Then that scared her so much that at 5:30 this morning

94
00:04:00,639 --> 00:04:01,960
she ran to the study room to do practice problems

95
00:04:03,759 --> 00:04:04,120
We're leaving

96
00:04:04,319 --> 00:04:04,639
Bye

97
00:04:04,639 --> 00:04:04,960
Okay

98
00:04:05,280 --> 00:04:05,960
Bye-bye, Guifang

99
00:04:05,960 --> 00:04:06,520
Bye-bye, Fang'er

100
00:04:11,439 --> 00:04:14,360
If you don't become a grad student, you'll have to research childbirth

101
00:04:29,600 --> 00:04:35,480
Ones, tens, hundreds, thousands, ten thousands, hundred thousands.

102
00:04:40,360 --> 00:04:41,879
Quick, quick, quick! Run!

103
00:04:42,439 --> 00:04:42,920
Okay.

104
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:44,639
Speed up.

105
00:04:44,959 --> 00:04:47,079
The thing is, I really never expected...

106
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,399
That I, Kong Xiaocan...

107
00:04:48,759 --> 00:04:51,040
Would actually become a Demolition heir in my lifetime.

108
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,399
Move out within 120 days of receiving payment.

109
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,199
Demolition heir, let's find a place.

110
00:04:56,439 --> 00:04:57,600
Wait, why aren't you going?

111
00:04:58,920 --> 00:05:02,120
Well, I have a very unexpected injury right now.

112
00:05:02,519 --> 00:05:03,800
I'm in extremely poor health.

113
00:05:04,439 --> 00:05:05,199
Hello? Mom?

114
00:05:10,199 --> 00:05:11,160
Good Mom. You're really something.

115
00:05:11,920 --> 00:05:12,680
No one cares about me.

116
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:13,800
I'm just a little weed.

117
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,439
Stinky weed.

118
00:05:18,439 --> 00:05:19,279
Take five, everyone.

119
00:05:19,639 --> 00:05:20,879
Drink some water if you need to.

120
00:05:31,839 --> 00:05:32,639
I unscrewed it for you.

121
00:05:36,399 --> 00:05:38,399
See? I'm pretty good at caring for people, right?

122
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,759
But no one cares about me.

123
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:42,480
Especially my mom.

124
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:43,279
Seriously.

125
00:05:43,639 --> 00:05:44,399
She's never home.

126
00:05:44,399 --> 00:05:46,319
She's probably already forgotten...

127
00:05:46,519 --> 00:05:47,160
Her identity as a mother.

128
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:48,000
The attitude she has when talking to me...

129
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,480
My fridge at home...

130
00:05:49,480 --> 00:05:51,079
That ice hasn't been scraped in three years.

131
00:05:51,079 --> 00:05:52,279
It's as thick as a heel.

132
00:05:52,279 --> 00:05:53,000
It's not my fault.

133
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Because it's gotten so thick...

134
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,199
You can't fit groceries in anymore.

135
00:05:55,199 --> 00:05:56,000
So I have to order takeout.

136
00:05:56,079 --> 00:05:57,399
And with food safety issues these days...

137
00:05:57,399 --> 00:05:58,879
What if I die from food poisoning?

138
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:00,600
Don't you think?

139
00:06:06,839 --> 00:06:09,199
When you just go "Mmhmm," you're just humoring me.

140
00:06:09,199 --> 00:06:10,079
You weren't listening, were you?

141
00:06:10,199 --> 00:06:10,800
I was listening.

142
00:06:10,800 --> 00:06:11,560
What did I just say?

143
00:06:13,959 --> 00:06:14,480
Heel.

144
00:06:17,319 --> 00:06:18,519
That ice is really thick.

145
00:06:18,759 --> 00:06:19,839
It's not that I'm paranoid.

146
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,839
In my condition, and you not telling me the cause...

147
00:06:21,959 --> 00:06:23,160
Scraping ice is also dangerous.

148
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:25,800
There's difluoromethane in the fridge.

149
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,000
If you nick the pipe even a little...

150
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:27,680
It could easily explode.

151
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:28,439
What if I die from...

152
00:06:29,680 --> 00:06:30,240
That's impossible.

153
00:06:30,879 --> 00:06:31,839
And that frozen fish...

154
00:06:32,199 --> 00:06:33,720
There's bacteria on frozen fish.

155
00:06:33,920 --> 00:06:35,959
If my hand gets infected by the bacteria...

156
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,279
Best case, amputation.

157
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,680
Worst case, sepsis.

158
00:06:43,399 --> 00:06:44,079
Really? This...

159
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:45,800
Is this it?

160
00:06:47,319 --> 00:06:48,079
Look at your face.

161
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:50,519
Good thing it's not. Quick, knock on wood.

162
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,399
Don't die of sepsis.

163
00:06:51,399 --> 00:06:52,360
That's an ugly way to die.

164
00:06:54,160 --> 00:06:54,600
What are you doing?

165
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:56,079
Covering it like that...

166
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:58,199
Trying to make the bacteria more comfortable?

167
00:07:01,319 --> 00:07:01,920
Where's the wound?

168
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:02,639
It's...

169
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,560
The wound... where is it?

170
00:07:06,959 --> 00:07:07,480
It migrated.

171
00:07:11,319 --> 00:07:12,240
No, it healed.

172
00:07:17,079 --> 00:07:17,759
Later...

173
00:07:18,439 --> 00:07:19,279
Come with me somewhere.

174
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:24,480
Me?

175
00:07:25,879 --> 00:07:26,879
A Fu needs to see you.

176
00:07:34,480 --> 00:07:34,839
No,

177
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:36,240
what's it like up there?

178
00:07:36,720 --> 00:07:39,439
The alien base must be really flashy.

179
00:07:39,439 --> 00:07:41,199
Is it like when a door opens,

180
00:07:41,199 --> 00:07:43,800
it's all white and floating like in the movies?

181
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,319
Are their true forms disgusting?

182
00:07:45,439 --> 00:07:46,480
Do they look like that kind of...

183
00:07:47,160 --> 00:07:48,680
You watch too many TV dramas, don't you?

184
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:50,000
No, it's normal.

185
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,120
You'll see once you go up.

186
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:55,120
Xiaocan.

187
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,439
Dear Can.

188
00:07:58,680 --> 00:07:59,199
Please come in.

189
00:08:02,399 --> 00:08:03,560
How is the situation here?

190
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:05,959
Did the esteemed Ms. Lin Xurui explain it to you?

191
00:08:07,480 --> 00:08:08,000
It doesn't matter.

192
00:08:08,199 --> 00:08:10,759
Allow me to explain it to you again.

193
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:13,680
The esteemed and wise Ms. Lin Xurui

194
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,759
has already introduced to us

195
00:08:14,759 --> 00:08:17,279
the details regarding the Human Shopping Festival.

196
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,360
I realized that in our project,

197
00:08:23,519 --> 00:08:25,000
there is one thing missing the most.

198
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,639
That is publicity.

199
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,920
So, after a meeting decision,

200
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:37,440
we decided to hire you, Mr. Kong Xiaocan,

201
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:40,759
as the Life Energy Exchange plan's

202
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:42,919
spokesperson.

203
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:49,600
Where'd he learn to talk like this?

204
00:08:49,720 --> 00:08:50,480
Let me introduce to you...

205
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,399
Please allow me

206
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:59,840
to formally introduce my race to you two.

207
00:09:06,399 --> 00:09:07,799
So you are...

208
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:11,600
located less than five light-years from Earth

209
00:09:11,600 --> 00:09:12,480
in Centaurus,

210
00:09:13,039 --> 00:09:15,639
on the planet designated B2526.

211
00:09:15,919 --> 00:09:17,240
That is our home planet.

212
00:09:19,360 --> 00:09:22,240
We are such advanced and elegant beings.

213
00:09:22,960 --> 00:09:24,440
But we possess a metabolic system

214
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:26,879
with an exceptionally low conversion rate.

215
00:09:27,480 --> 00:09:28,840
To live long,

216
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:33,399
we must be slow, slow, slow.

217
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:36,679
This has seriously impacted our planet's development.

218
00:09:37,039 --> 00:09:38,440
Therefore, our Expeditionary Department

219
00:09:38,519 --> 00:09:39,919
stepped out of B2526,

220
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,279
stepped out of Centaurus,

221
00:09:41,399 --> 00:09:43,840
and ventured into the Milky Way and the vast universe,

222
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:47,440
seeking life energy that allows us to leap forward.

223
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:50,200
The life energy on Earth,

224
00:09:50,399 --> 00:09:52,360
resilient, vigorous, and endless,

225
00:09:52,559 --> 00:09:54,639
will bring to our planet's life energy development

226
00:09:54,879 --> 00:09:55,679
and even to

227
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:58,440
the entire universe's life energy trading system

228
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,120
a tremendous transformation.

229
00:10:01,039 --> 00:10:03,039
We will make good use of Earth's resources

230
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,159
to advance life on our planet.

231
00:10:05,360 --> 00:10:08,080
We will also promote the development of life energy trading,

232
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:10,159
from P to A to B to C,

233
00:10:10,159 --> 00:10:12,159
to the innovation of Little Turtles.

234
00:10:13,039 --> 00:10:13,960
One small step for us,

235
00:10:14,240 --> 00:10:16,559
one giant leap for B2526.

236
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:19,039
We bring life energy back to our home planet,

237
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:21,279
and leave the lessons from wealth exchange

238
00:10:21,759 --> 00:10:23,000
to the universe.

239
00:10:28,200 --> 00:10:29,720
So this is your true form.

240
00:10:30,559 --> 00:10:31,759
Then those ninjas,

241
00:10:31,759 --> 00:10:33,480
Prime Ministers, and Immortals,

242
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,120
and that Qigong school are all your people?

243
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:36,720
Those are just fans.

244
00:10:38,279 --> 00:10:38,799
The Kingdom of Turtles.

245
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:41,919
Can it understand me?

246
00:10:42,559 --> 00:10:42,919
He can.

247
00:10:43,879 --> 00:10:44,639
He even spoke.

248
00:10:44,759 --> 00:10:45,159
What did he say?

249
00:10:46,279 --> 00:10:48,879
He said Ms. Xu Rui is very beautiful.

250
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:50,559
What about me?

251
00:10:52,159 --> 00:10:52,720
He said...

252
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:54,399
Okay, come on.

253
00:10:54,399 --> 00:10:55,200
Let's look at the next place.

254
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,039
Okay, thanks, thanks.

255
00:10:57,159 --> 00:10:57,519
Over here.

256
00:11:03,159 --> 00:11:03,480
This...

257
00:11:03,799 --> 00:11:04,840
This is that ninja, right?

258
00:11:05,320 --> 00:11:07,879
This is the statue of our planet's ruler,

259
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,039
the Green King.

260
00:11:09,600 --> 00:11:10,159
So green.

261
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,039
And over here is the office area.

262
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:14,279
Are these all Turtle People?

263
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:17,039
How could these be Turtle People?

264
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,240
Look at the people here.

265
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,399
Slacking off,

266
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,639
playing on their phones,

267
00:11:20,639 --> 00:11:21,559
zoning out.

268
00:11:21,759 --> 00:11:23,159
These are things only you humans do.

269
00:11:23,159 --> 00:11:25,039
True. No wonder they don't look like turtles.

270
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:25,679
Except for you.

271
00:11:26,879 --> 00:11:28,679
So they work for you?

272
00:11:29,559 --> 00:11:30,639
They are just ordinary people.

273
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:33,279
This is just an ordinary agricultural company.

274
00:11:33,519 --> 00:11:34,559
Do they know about you?

275
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:35,799
No, they don't.

276
00:11:36,080 --> 00:11:39,600
Only the Expeditionary Department over there are our people.

277
00:11:40,279 --> 00:11:41,360
Hidden in plain sight.

278
00:11:44,279 --> 00:11:46,440
The partners in the Expeditionary Department heard you were coming,

279
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:47,399
and they were thrilled.

280
00:11:47,519 --> 00:11:48,559
They really admire you.

281
00:11:48,559 --> 00:11:49,480
They all want your autograph.

282
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:50,200
I stopped them.

283
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:51,600
Then I... I'll leave a bit later.

284
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,120
