563
00:23:24,759 --> 00:23:25,799
If it doesn't get sun, it just...

564
00:23:26,240 --> 00:23:26,640
Right?

565
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,599
Plus, it's easy to get depressed.

566
00:23:28,599 --> 00:23:29,440
Once depressed, he just...

567
00:23:30,599 --> 00:23:31,440
Good thing this is the second floor.

568
00:23:32,359 --> 00:23:32,839
Alright then.

569
00:23:32,960 --> 00:23:34,759
Let's check out the bathroom, okay?

570
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:36,799
Come, look how clean this bathroom is.

571
00:23:38,839 --> 00:23:41,920
This design of yours is quite interesting.

572
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:42,640
Yes.

573
00:23:43,079 --> 00:23:45,000
But... do I shower while using the toilet?

574
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:45,759
Or use the toilet while showering?

575
00:23:46,559 --> 00:23:47,559
You need wet and dry separation.

576
00:23:47,559 --> 00:23:49,240
I'll get soaked just using the toilet here.

577
00:23:49,759 --> 00:23:51,880
Most importantly, your pipes are aging.

578
00:23:51,880 --> 00:23:52,279
Look.

579
00:23:53,079 --> 00:23:54,200
What if this explodes?

580
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,200
Well then, come, let's look at the secondary bedroom.

581
00:23:57,240 --> 00:23:57,519
Okay.

582
00:23:58,559 --> 00:23:59,200
It's also quite comfortable.

583
00:23:59,839 --> 00:24:00,200
Seeing this,

584
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:01,720
I realize a more obvious problem.

585
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:02,599
What problem?

586
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:03,440
This is the second floor.

587
00:24:03,559 --> 00:24:04,000
Yes.

588
00:24:04,119 --> 00:24:05,559
The second floor is easy for thieves and criminals to enter.

589
00:24:05,559 --> 00:24:07,160
That would be too dangerous.

590
00:24:07,319 --> 00:24:07,920
No, sir.

591
00:24:07,920 --> 00:24:09,240
There are guardrails here.

592
00:24:09,599 --> 00:24:10,640
What era is this?

593
00:24:10,640 --> 00:24:12,359
These guardrails are just for show.

594
00:24:13,559 --> 00:24:14,279
No, sir.

595
00:24:14,680 --> 00:24:17,119
With your budget and the issues you just mentioned,

596
00:24:17,119 --> 00:24:18,880
I can only solve one at most.

597
00:24:20,359 --> 00:24:20,880
Pass?

598
00:24:22,200 --> 00:24:23,079
Pass. Okay, no problem.

599
00:24:23,279 --> 00:24:24,480
I have more apartments here.

600
00:24:24,480 --> 00:24:25,359
I'll take you to see more.

601
00:24:25,640 --> 00:24:26,359
What do you say, Mom?

602
00:24:28,960 --> 00:24:29,519
Mom.

603
00:24:34,559 --> 00:24:35,200
Still no good.

604
00:24:35,920 --> 00:24:37,240
This one has a balcony.

605
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:38,680
North-south facing.

606
00:24:38,680 --> 00:24:40,559
Opposite this, facing that restaurant building.

607
00:24:40,559 --> 00:24:41,920
Is the Feng Shui bad?

608
00:24:42,799 --> 00:24:43,920
Do I even deserve to live here?

609
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:45,000
Are there listings across the street?

610
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,000
Yes.

611
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:47,960
But across the street is high-end housing.

612
00:24:48,640 --> 00:24:49,319
To be honest,

613
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:52,319
Look, the price is indeed a bit high.

614
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:54,599
Here, a two-bedroom is three thousand.

615
00:24:54,599 --> 00:24:55,400
And it has a big balcony.

616
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:57,759
Over there, three thousand only gets you a single room.

617
00:24:58,440 --> 00:24:59,359
Same lake view,

618
00:24:59,480 --> 00:25:00,279
Same greenery,

619
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:01,640
This side is still a better deal.

620
00:25:02,799 --> 00:25:03,480
Take me to have a look.

621
00:25:04,039 --> 00:25:04,559
Okay, sure, sure.

622
00:25:04,559 --> 00:25:05,400
Wait, wait, wait.

623
00:25:05,599 --> 00:25:06,240
What are you doing?

624
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:07,960
Are you getting carried away?

625
00:25:08,119 --> 00:25:09,359
We should live within our means.

626
00:25:09,359 --> 00:25:10,480
How much money do we have?

627
00:25:10,480 --> 00:25:11,319
We don't usually...

628
00:25:11,319 --> 00:25:12,440
We just need a place to live.

629
00:25:12,440 --> 00:25:13,920
The apartment is rented,

630
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:15,119
but life is our own.

631
00:25:15,720 --> 00:25:16,160
Fine, fine.

632
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:16,839
Let's go look.

633
00:25:16,839 --> 00:25:18,119
That's right. Come, come, this way please.

634
00:25:18,119 --> 00:25:18,799
Keep up.

635
00:25:29,079 --> 00:25:30,559
I've looked at so many places.

636
00:25:31,359 --> 00:25:32,559
And I still think that one is the best.

637
00:25:32,839 --> 00:25:35,039
Both bedrooms face the sun.

638
00:25:35,440 --> 00:25:37,440
And open up the living room and kitchen completely.

639
00:25:38,720 --> 00:25:40,680
If you dare rent this place for 7,500 a month...

640
00:25:40,680 --> 00:25:42,519
I... I'll run away from home immediately.

641
00:25:42,519 --> 00:25:43,240
I'm putting my foot down.

642
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,559
Mom has it all planned out for you.

643
00:25:45,119 --> 00:25:45,839
That apartment...

644
00:25:45,839 --> 00:25:47,119
The full price is 3.6 million.

645
00:25:47,559 --> 00:25:49,640
I'll pay the down payment for you first.

646
00:25:49,799 --> 00:25:50,519
As for the monthly mortgage...

647
00:25:50,759 --> 00:25:51,160
Wait a minute.

648
00:25:52,039 --> 00:25:52,839
You want to buy it?

649
00:25:53,039 --> 00:25:53,440
Yeah.

650
00:25:57,319 --> 00:25:58,640
For most of my life...

651
00:25:58,640 --> 00:25:59,480
I've had just two goals.

652
00:25:59,880 --> 00:26:01,559
One was putting you through college.

653
00:26:01,920 --> 00:26:03,559
The other was buying you a home for your marriage.

654
00:26:04,279 --> 00:26:05,920
That's about all I can do.

655
00:26:07,079 --> 00:26:08,880
Tell me, since I'm your mother...

656
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:10,839
I have to buy you a place, don't I?

657
00:26:11,640 --> 00:26:12,960
It has to have at least two bedrooms.

658
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:15,759
Whether you and Xu Rui have kids or not...

659
00:26:15,759 --> 00:26:16,599
That doesn't matter.

660
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:18,519
I won't pressure you.

661
00:26:19,359 --> 00:26:20,720
I won't live with you anyway.

662
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:24,319
Of the two rooms, one can be a study.

663
00:26:24,839 --> 00:26:26,119
When guests come, use it as a guest room.

664
00:26:26,559 --> 00:26:29,240
For example, if Li Wai and Xiaoyin have a fight...

665
00:26:29,240 --> 00:26:30,759
You can take Li Wai in, right?

666
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:34,319
You can also get a puppy.

667
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:36,359
A kitten works too.

668
00:26:36,839 --> 00:26:37,640
Cats are clean.

669
00:26:37,640 --> 00:26:38,519
They're easy to take care of.

670
00:26:42,240 --> 00:26:43,519
You've really planned it all out.

671
00:26:43,799 --> 00:26:44,559
What about yourself?

672
00:26:44,960 --> 00:26:45,799
Living in the dorms?

673
00:26:46,039 --> 00:26:46,680
With Professor Wang?

674
00:26:46,680 --> 00:26:48,359
Living on a subsidy of over a thousand a month?

675
00:26:48,480 --> 00:26:50,160
Just tell me, why bother?

676
00:26:50,480 --> 00:26:52,519
We finally have some money from the demolition.

677
00:26:52,720 --> 00:26:54,279
And now you're spending so much on a house.

678
00:26:54,279 --> 00:26:55,599
Won't we become mortgage slaves again? You...

679
00:26:55,599 --> 00:26:56,119
No, no.

680
00:26:56,119 --> 00:26:56,680
I don't need that.

681
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:57,440
Listen to me.

682
00:26:58,160 --> 00:26:59,519
Agronomy isn't that poor.

683
00:27:00,160 --> 00:27:01,720
I got my internship salary today.

684
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,480
Guess how much.

685
00:27:02,920 --> 00:27:03,720
You get a salary?

686
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:04,200
How much?

687
00:27:04,480 --> 00:27:05,599
Eighty? A hundred?

688
00:27:06,599 --> 00:27:07,440
A month.

689
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:09,359
Thirteen thousand.

690
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:13,359
How much?

691
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:14,440
Thirteen thousand!

692
00:27:14,599 --> 00:27:15,400
Thirteen thousand.

693
00:27:15,480 --> 00:27:15,880
Yeah.

694
00:27:16,359 --> 00:27:18,079
That's why I said I'd buy you a house.

695
00:27:18,559 --> 00:27:19,599
I have money now.

696
00:27:21,839 --> 00:27:22,559
Don't doubt it.

697
00:27:22,559 --> 00:27:24,720
It's a big company, the prospects are great.

698
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:27,079
The net profit margin is 44.94 percent.

699
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:28,079
And the boss...

700
00:27:28,720 --> 00:27:29,960
The boss doesn't look very...

701
00:27:29,960 --> 00:27:30,720
Wait a minute. Alright, but...

702
00:27:30,720 --> 00:27:31,960
This doesn't sound reliable at all.

703
00:27:32,480 --> 00:27:33,440
Li Wai is a legit graduate.

704
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:35,440
And he can't even find a base salary of 4,000 now.

705
00:27:35,440 --> 00:27:36,680
You're an intern making thirteen thousand?

706
00:27:36,680 --> 00:27:38,279
Do you think that's reasonable? Is it reliable?

707
00:27:38,599 --> 00:27:39,640
What company? Tell me the name.

708
00:27:39,640 --> 00:27:40,720
Mom, you've been scammed.

709
00:27:40,720 --> 00:27:41,519
I'm going to check it out for you.

710
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:43,160
Wanxiang Denong.

711
00:27:43,519 --> 00:27:43,880
Wan...

712
00:27:46,359 --> 00:27:47,519
Guifang, we're off work now.

713
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:48,720
Okay, bye-bye.

714
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,200
Why is she working here?

715
00:28:07,200 --> 00:28:08,519
She's a ticking time bomb!

716
00:28:08,960 --> 00:28:10,599
I'm asking you. Is this your doing?

717
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:12,119
What intern makes thirteen thousand?

718
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:13,559
How could it be me?

719
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,039
I don't even work here.

720
00:28:15,559 --> 00:28:16,680
You don't work here?

721
00:28:21,799 --> 00:28:23,079
You're lying. You don't work here...

722
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:23,799
You *do* work here.

723
00:28:23,799 --> 00:28:24,680
How could you not know about her?

724
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,599
I don't have a desk job here.

725
00:28:26,599 --> 00:28:27,559
This has nothing to do with me.

726
00:28:27,559 --> 00:28:28,279
No matter what,

727
00:28:28,279 --> 00:28:29,200
get her out of here right now.

728
00:28:30,279 --> 00:28:31,279
How am I supposed to get her out?

729
00:28:31,559 --> 00:28:33,079
She... she knows me.

730
00:28:33,079 --> 00:28:33,680
Have you forgotten?

731
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:34,880
I'm that...

732
00:28:35,640 --> 00:28:37,119
your dear son Kong Xiaocan...

733
00:28:37,119 --> 00:28:38,359
stole medicine from our lab...

734
00:28:38,359 --> 00:28:39,039
Alright, alright.

735
00:28:39,640 --> 00:28:40,400
...doctor.

736
00:28:47,880 --> 00:28:48,960
If you don't get her out of here,

737
00:28:49,480 --> 00:28:51,160
I won't do the sharing session.

738
00:28:51,720 --> 00:28:53,440
Kong Xiaocan!

739
00:28:53,720 --> 00:28:56,240
That sharing session counts towards my performance!

740
00:28:56,240 --> 00:28:57,519
I'm begging you, okay?

741
00:28:57,519 --> 00:28:59,319
Get her out of here, fast.

742
00:28:59,319 --> 00:28:59,960
It's a deal.

743
00:29:04,440 --> 00:29:05,640
Why did he agree so quickly?

744
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:10,960
Was he manipulating my mind just now?

745
00:29:13,160 --> 00:29:14,160
Humans are so smart.

746
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:43,200
If anything is unclear, ask me anytime later.

747
00:30:34,680 --> 00:30:35,440
Xiaocan

748
00:30:37,279 --> 00:30:38,200
What are you doing here?

749
00:30:38,759 --> 00:30:39,799
Well, you... I...

750
00:30:39,799 --> 00:30:40,400
Wait a second.

751
00:30:41,480 --> 00:30:42,160
Why are you here?

752
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:43,960
It's pouring rain.

753
00:30:43,960 --> 00:30:45,400
Isn't it only right for a son to pick up his mom?

754
00:30:45,440 --> 00:30:46,279
No, no, no.

755
00:30:46,279 --> 00:30:47,519
You want something. What is it?

756
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,039
Mom, you're being a bit cynic...

757
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:56,279
It's still warm.

758
00:30:56,359 --> 00:30:56,920
Yeah.

759
00:31:00,759 --> 00:31:01,160
Mom.

760
00:31:02,279 --> 00:31:05,279
What have you been doing at the company lately?

761
00:31:05,279 --> 00:31:06,319
Working overtime so late every day.

762
00:31:06,839 --> 00:31:07,599
Making money.

763
00:31:08,000 --> 00:31:09,319
The overtime pay is really high.

764
00:31:10,960 --> 00:31:14,240
You haven't met any strange people lately, have you?

765
00:31:14,799 --> 00:31:15,640
Strange people?

766
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:18,680
Actually, yes.

767
00:31:20,240 --> 00:31:20,960
They're everywhere.

768
00:31:22,799 --> 00:31:24,319
No, I mean, they really are quite strange.

769
00:31:24,640 --> 00:31:26,279
A job with such a high salary,

770
00:31:26,279 --> 00:31:27,599
why doesn't anyone put their heart into it?

771
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,839
You're the weird one now, not them.

772
00:31:31,440 --> 00:31:32,079
I'm weird?

773
00:31:32,079 --> 00:31:34,519
Everyone's into "lying flat" these days, right?

774
00:31:35,640 --> 00:31:37,279
Mom, look at you.

775
00:31:37,480 --> 00:31:38,599
You're twenty years old now.

776
00:31:38,599 --> 00:31:39,559
Working for someone else.

777
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,720
By thirty, you'll just be a glorified employee.

778
00:31:41,720 --> 00:31:42,640
Wait, wait, wait.

779
00:31:43,240 --> 00:31:44,440
I've heard this speech before.

780
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:45,279
I don't want to hear it a second time.

781
00:31:45,559 --> 00:31:46,559
The words are rough, but the logic holds.

782
00:31:47,200 --> 00:31:48,880
Isn't your life goal to plant saplings?

783
00:31:48,880 --> 00:31:49,599
To do scientific research?

784
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:51,240
Why are you here just making money, Mom?

785
00:31:51,759 --> 00:31:53,920
As a lucky person who got a second chance at life,

786
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:54,400
right?

787
00:31:54,880 --> 00:31:56,200
Normally, people in your situation...

788
00:31:56,559 --> 00:31:58,839
At the very least, they'd go to college properly,

789
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:00,359
enjoy doing what they love.

790
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:01,599
Or at best,

791
00:32:02,759 --> 00:32:04,400
take our demolition compensation, right?

792
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:05,079
Travel the world.

793
00:32:05,079 --> 00:32:05,640
Enjoy life.

794
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,519
Eat good food, right?

795
00:32:06,519 --> 00:32:08,039
If you keep going on like this,

796
00:32:08,039 --> 00:32:08,880
I'm telling you,

797
00:32:09,480 --> 00:32:10,240
your pancreatic cancer...

798
00:32:10,240 --> 00:32:12,079
will show up five years earlier than it did before.

799
00:32:13,119 --> 00:32:13,680
Don't hit me!

800
00:32:13,680 --> 00:32:14,000
I'm telling you.

801
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:14,680
I'm telling you the truth.

802
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:15,839
Don't ignore good advice just because it hurts.

803
00:32:20,720 --> 00:32:21,319
Xiaocan.

804
00:32:23,279 --> 00:32:25,559
When Mom brought you to this city back then,

805
00:32:27,359 --> 00:32:28,279
it wasn't like this.

806
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:31,759
It's changed a lot for the better.

807
00:32:33,720 --> 00:32:36,000
When Mom came here back then,

808
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:37,720
I had less than four hundred yuan to my name.

809
00:32:38,839 --> 00:32:41,319
My wallet was stolen as soon as I got off the train.

810
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,759
Luckily, I had hidden some money in my shoe.

811
00:32:46,279 --> 00:32:47,720
I remember holding you,

812
00:32:48,519 --> 00:32:50,319
standing in front of that square.

813
00:32:52,640 --> 00:32:54,599
Mom didn't know where to catch the bus.

814
00:32:54,599 --> 00:32:55,880
I wasn't familiar with the area either.

815
00:32:57,640 --> 00:32:58,400
At that moment,

816
00:33:01,279 --> 00:33:02,519
I didn't feel much for myself,

817
00:33:03,480 --> 00:33:05,240
but I felt so sorry for my son.

818
00:33:06,920 --> 00:33:07,720
I swore then,

819
00:33:08,519 --> 00:33:10,200
I would give you a good life.

820
00:33:11,839 --> 00:33:12,880
So for the past twenty years,

821
00:33:13,240 --> 00:33:14,519
Mom worked desperately to make money.

822
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:16,400
Bought an apartment.

823
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:17,880
Saved up a little money.

824
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:20,119
But who could have guessed,

825
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,640
I'd end up getting seriously ill later on?

826
00:33:26,319 --> 00:33:26,960
But Mom,

827
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:29,000
none of us expected,

828
00:33:29,559 --> 00:33:31,359
that our family would get a windfall from demolition compensation.

829
00:33:37,000 --> 00:33:37,519
Son,

830
00:33:39,880 --> 00:33:41,119
but this demolition compensation

831
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:43,559
isn't enough to support

832
00:33:43,559 --> 00:33:45,359
the so-called wonderful rest of your life.

833
00:33:49,039 --> 00:33:49,640
Mom knows

834
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:51,960
you think I'm living

835
00:33:52,160 --> 00:33:53,720
a repetitive life, day after day.

836
00:33:54,119 --> 00:33:55,200
But actually, that's not true.

837
00:33:56,039 --> 00:33:57,039
I used to make money

838
00:33:57,680 --> 00:33:58,759
hoping that the two of us

839
00:33:58,759 --> 00:34:00,279
could survive in this city.

840
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:02,240
Now I make money

841
00:34:02,599 --> 00:34:04,359
hoping that we can live well.

842
00:34:07,119 --> 00:34:08,599
Mom has fulfilled her dream, too.

843
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:09,840
I went to college,

844
00:34:10,199 --> 00:34:11,599
and using the knowledge I learned,

845
00:34:11,599 --> 00:34:12,960
I'm working here and making money now.

846
00:34:13,039 --> 00:34:13,760
Isn't that great?

847
00:34:14,519 --> 00:34:16,400
Mom is doing what she loves.

848
00:34:17,079 --> 00:34:19,119
This is what Mom considers the best days.

849
00:34:23,679 --> 00:34:24,199
Besides,

850
00:34:25,000 --> 00:34:26,679
it seems now there is also a

851
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:28,480
son who is slowly growing up.

852
00:34:29,280 --> 00:34:30,000
How wonderful.

853
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:31,760
Right?

854
00:34:37,679 --> 00:34:38,199
Mom

855
00:34:39,679 --> 00:34:42,360
Are you truly happy right now?

856
00:34:48,039 --> 00:34:48,639
Of course.

857
00:34:53,199 --> 00:34:53,719
I've got your back.

858
00:34:55,079 --> 00:34:55,440
Let's go home.

859
00:34:58,800 --> 00:35:01,079
Didn't I come here to persuade Mom to quit Wanxiang?

860
00:35:01,559 --> 00:35:02,480
How did I end up switching sides?

861
00:35:07,639 --> 00:35:09,039
It's too hard to find a job this year.

862
00:35:09,280 --> 00:35:10,039
Li Wai still hasn't...

863
00:35:10,039 --> 00:35:11,480
...received a single offer letter yet.

864
00:35:12,159 --> 00:35:13,519
He was joking that...

865
00:35:14,280 --> 00:35:15,679
...he wouldn't do his thesis defense this year.

866
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:17,280
Just slack off and defer graduation for a year.

867
00:35:17,719 --> 00:35:18,239
But then...

868
00:35:18,719 --> 00:35:20,719
The third-ranked student in his class failed four subjects on purpose.

869
00:35:21,239 --> 00:35:22,719
Now Li Wai can't even get a spot to defer graduation.

870
00:35:23,119 --> 00:35:25,000
I remember Li Wai's grades were pretty good, weren't they?

871
00:35:25,000 --> 00:35:25,440
Yeah.

872
00:35:25,719 --> 00:35:27,199
His professional skills are great.

873
00:35:27,199 --> 00:35:28,320
But his comprehensive score isn't.

874
00:35:28,440 --> 00:35:29,280
Especially PE.

875
00:35:29,599 --> 00:35:31,199
He can't even outrun me in the physical test.

876
00:35:31,400 --> 00:35:32,480
For real?

877
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:33,440
You bet.

878
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:34,639
He's hopeless.

879
00:35:35,039 --> 00:35:35,639
Seriously.

880
00:35:36,199 --> 00:35:36,760
Guifang.

881
00:35:37,199 --> 00:35:39,559
I just noticed you bought a lot of stuff today.

882
00:35:39,559 --> 00:35:40,239
Yeah.

883
00:35:40,239 --> 00:35:41,440
All for Xiaocan, right?

884
00:35:41,440 --> 00:35:41,960
That's right.

885
00:35:42,920 --> 00:35:43,840
You really are an intern now.

886
00:35:43,840 --> 00:35:44,599
You've got money.

887
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:47,800
Actually, agronomy isn't a career black hole.

888
00:35:48,280 --> 00:35:50,719
Look at seeds, fertilizers, and pesticides.

889
00:35:50,719 --> 00:35:51,920
The salaries are pretty high.

890
00:35:52,320 --> 00:35:53,599
If you guys don't switch careers...

891
00:35:53,679 --> 00:35:55,039
...it's actually quite lucrative.

892
00:35:55,440 --> 00:35:58,039
Xiaoyin and I opening an online shop is also lucrative.

893
00:35:59,039 --> 00:36:00,840
But are you happy?

894
00:36:01,440 --> 00:36:02,079
I am.

895
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:03,280
You guys have no idea.

896
00:36:03,519 --> 00:36:04,400
A couple of days ago...

897
00:36:04,400 --> 00:36:06,039
...when I was reporting to my boss...

898
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:07,840
...it was all English research papers.

899
00:36:08,320 --> 00:36:09,119
After I finished organizing them...

900
00:36:09,119 --> 00:36:11,079
...I stood by the printer...

901
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:12,760
...and watched those sheets...

902
00:36:12,920 --> 00:36:13,880
...of Chinese-English comparison tables...

903
00:36:13,880 --> 00:36:14,679
...popping out.

904
00:36:15,280 --> 00:36:17,480
I can't tell you how accomplished I felt.

905
00:36:17,920 --> 00:36:19,239
I had just one thought in my mind.

906
00:36:19,239 --> 00:36:19,679
I thought...

907
00:36:20,159 --> 00:36:21,480
..."I am so awesome."

908
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,920
"I can actually understand all this."

909
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:28,039
But...

910
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:31,480
It's written all over your face. "But."

911
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:37,280
But...

912
00:36:39,119 --> 00:36:40,760
Domestic seeds are sold by weight.

913
00:36:41,239 --> 00:36:43,159
Imported seeds are sold by the grain.

914
00:36:44,119 --> 00:36:45,119
Imported seeds...

915
00:36:45,199 --> 00:36:46,119
...have monopolized the market.

916
00:36:46,880 --> 00:36:47,960
Our company opts for convenience.

917
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:50,119
They don't give domestic breeding a single chance.

918
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,719
In the two years I spent with Professor Wang...

919
00:36:53,679 --> 00:36:55,159
...we knocked on doors everywhere but couldn't get in.

920
00:36:56,280 --> 00:36:56,960
Now...

921
00:36:58,199 --> 00:36:59,400
...I've become someone on the inside.

922
00:37:00,159 --> 00:37:02,360
Sometimes I even have to block the door.

923
00:37:07,239 --> 00:37:08,719
But now, without hesitation...

924
00:37:08,719 --> 00:37:10,239
...I can buy clothes and shoes for Xiaocan.

925
00:37:10,320 --> 00:37:10,760
Look.

926
00:37:11,199 --> 00:37:13,119
And I can buy so many at once.

927
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,519
I wouldn't have dared to imagine that before.

928
00:37:14,519 --> 00:37:16,440
How could I have known I'd earn this much money?

929
00:37:17,639 --> 00:37:18,800
Our hearts just aren't in it.

930
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:19,760
If we don't do it, then we don't.

931
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:23,320
Fang'er, you really need to think this through.

932
00:37:29,119 --> 00:37:32,000
A loving heart brings life energy.

933
00:37:32,519 --> 00:37:34,320
Let's welcome today's guest...

934
00:37:34,719 --> 00:37:37,840
...one of the Century's Top Ten Filial Sons, Mr. Kong Xiaocan.

935
00:37:45,920 --> 00:37:46,840
It really brings back memories

936
00:37:46,840 --> 00:37:47,320
Please sit

937
00:37:48,840 --> 00:37:50,000
Mr. Kong's story,

938
00:37:50,000 --> 00:37:51,440
I'm sure everyone knows it

939
00:37:51,760 --> 00:37:53,199
He paid fifty years of his own life

940
00:37:53,599 --> 00:37:55,440
in exchange for his mother's new life

941
00:37:56,480 --> 00:37:56,960
Mr. Kong,

942
00:37:57,280 --> 00:38:00,119
could you tell us what you were thinking at the time?

943
00:38:01,199 --> 00:38:05,119
I didn't really think much about it at the time

944
00:38:05,960 --> 00:38:07,440
Really? I don't believe it

945
00:38:08,719 --> 00:38:09,920
I really didn't think much

946
00:38:10,440 --> 00:38:12,599
So it was a completely subconscious act

947
00:38:13,480 --> 00:38:15,039
You saw your mother in pain,

948
00:38:15,039 --> 00:38:15,920
and felt unwilling to accept it,

949
00:38:16,119 --> 00:38:17,719
so subconsciously,

950
00:38:17,920 --> 00:38:19,840
you exchanged fifty years of your life

951
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:20,400
Right?

952
00:38:21,480 --> 00:38:21,960
Maybe

953
00:38:22,840 --> 00:38:24,239
That is truly so touching

954
00:38:24,239 --> 00:38:25,000
You are truly amazing

955
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:25,480
Thank you

956
00:38:25,880 --> 00:38:26,559
So, Mr. Kong,

957
00:38:26,719 --> 00:38:28,559
what was the driving force behind all this?

958
00:38:29,519 --> 00:38:30,599
Driving force...

959
00:38:31,039 --> 00:38:34,079
Maybe I felt that as a son...

960
00:38:34,079 --> 00:38:34,880
I was too much of a failure

961
00:38:36,159 --> 00:38:37,719
No, as a son...

962
00:38:37,719 --> 00:38:38,679
I was too incompetent

963
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:40,559
As a son...

964
00:38:40,559 --> 00:38:43,320
I caused my mother too much worry

965
00:38:43,519 --> 00:38:44,639
Well, not exactly

966
00:38:44,639 --> 00:38:45,880
So you resolutely

967
00:38:45,880 --> 00:38:47,119
exchanged your own energy

968
00:38:47,119 --> 00:38:47,880
for your mother

969
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:49,039
Not really... I'm right, aren't I?

970
00:38:49,920 --> 00:38:51,840
Not entirely. I'm okay

971
00:38:52,400 --> 00:38:53,880
I wasn't that much of a troublemaker, actually

972
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:54,840
Not that troublesome

973
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:56,519
Then can you talk about the troublesome parts?

974
00:38:58,199 --> 00:38:59,480
I was never really troublesome

975
00:38:59,480 --> 00:39:00,440
According to rumors,

976
00:39:00,840 --> 00:39:01,360
Kong Xiaocan

977
00:39:01,360 --> 00:39:03,679
has been a troublesome child since he was young

978
00:39:04,400 --> 00:39:05,480
He stole eggplants from home,

979
00:39:05,719 --> 00:39:07,239
stole the neighbor's pressure cooker,

980
00:39:07,480 --> 00:39:08,920
and even scammed his mother out of money,

981
00:39:08,920 --> 00:39:09,960
then secretly went traveling,

982
00:39:10,079 --> 00:39:11,000
and bought sneakers

983
00:39:11,360 --> 00:39:12,599
Stuck with such a child,

984
00:39:12,719 --> 00:39:14,760
his mother fell ill over time

985
00:39:15,400 --> 00:39:16,320
She went to the hospital for a checkup,

986
00:39:16,320 --> 00:39:18,239
and at first thought it was just ordinary

987
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:19,320
stomach trouble

988
00:39:19,519 --> 00:39:21,440
But checks revealed it was severe

989
00:39:21,719 --> 00:39:22,440
late-stage pancreatic cancer

990
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:24,199
It really makes one feel re-

991
00:39:24,199 --> 00:39:24,719
gretful

992
00:39:30,159 --> 00:39:31,920
Isn't that... hasn't everyone heard that?

993
00:39:32,599 --> 00:39:33,440
How could this happen?

994
00:39:33,599 --> 00:39:35,599
It's truly heartbreaking, isn't it?

995
00:39:35,960 --> 00:39:38,599
Actually, I feel...

996
00:39:38,599 --> 00:39:40,679
I still feel very guilty

997
00:39:42,159 --> 00:39:42,480
No

998
00:39:42,480 --> 00:39:44,480
I still have a lot of unwillingness in my heart

999
00:39:44,840 --> 00:39:45,400
But,

1000
00:39:45,400 --> 00:39:46,719
if I could have treated Mom

1001
00:39:46,719 --> 00:39:48,199
a little better back then,

1002
00:39:49,360 --> 00:39:51,719
maybe none of this would have happened

1003
00:39:52,199 --> 00:39:54,360
So you resolutely chose

1004
00:39:54,519 --> 00:39:56,480
to exchange your life energy

1005
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:59,320
to make his mother healthy again

1006
00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:01,000
It's truly so touching, isn't it?

1007
00:40:13,119 --> 00:40:15,639
Mr. Kong, you exchanged fifty years of life

1008
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:17,239
Does that mean you don't want to live anymore?

1009
00:40:17,559 --> 00:40:18,000
Yes

1010
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,079
Isn't this what you wanted?

1011
00:40:24,960 --> 00:40:26,320
Everyone's simulation of human behavior

1012
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:27,440
still needs improvement

1013
00:40:27,639 --> 00:40:29,519
Now, four years have passed

1014
00:40:29,719 --> 00:40:30,119
Well?

1015
00:40:30,199 --> 00:40:32,000
What do you think of that choice now?

1016
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:34,760
Look

1017
00:40:35,280 --> 00:40:36,199
His hesitation

1018
00:40:36,320 --> 00:40:37,480
is telling us

1019
00:40:37,599 --> 00:40:40,639
that silence represents his loyalty

1020
00:40:41,239 --> 00:40:43,199
Death befalls all men alike

1021
00:40:43,800 --> 00:40:44,719
It may be lighter than a feather

1022
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:45,800
or heavier than Mount Tai

1023
00:40:46,280 --> 00:40:47,119
And Mr. Kong

1024
00:40:47,239 --> 00:40:50,079
chose a greater way

1025
00:40:50,320 --> 00:40:54,800
Let's give a round of applause to the filial son, Kong Xiaocan

1026
00:40:55,880 --> 00:40:56,360
Well said!

1027
00:40:56,679 --> 00:40:57,480
Good!

1028
00:40:58,599 --> 00:40:58,960
Good!

1029
00:40:59,159 --> 00:40:59,559
Good!

1030
00:40:59,920 --> 00:41:02,280
Let's wish him a life of one hundred and eighty years

1031
00:41:02,599 --> 00:41:03,679
Is this my real time?

1032
00:41:03,800 --> 00:41:04,639
You definitely won't live that long

1033
00:41:06,679 --> 00:41:07,840
Alright, everyone

1034
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:09,960
Are you Ms. Kong Guifang?

1035
00:41:12,679 --> 00:41:13,480
To think there are still

1036
00:41:13,480 --> 00:41:16,199
people other than insiders who know the details

1037
00:41:16,559 --> 00:41:18,360
You must have mixed feelings

1038
00:41:21,119 --> 00:41:21,760
Yes

1039
00:41:23,280 --> 00:41:24,679
At such a close distance

1040
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:26,760
what we can do

1041
00:41:27,599 --> 00:41:28,440
is very limited

1042
00:41:31,920 --> 00:41:33,679
As time passes

1043
00:41:35,239 --> 00:41:36,320
he will blame himself

1044
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:39,280
wondering why he has to die so early

1045
00:41:41,199 --> 00:41:42,719
He'll worry about what you'll do

1046
00:41:44,800 --> 00:41:45,800
He will constantly

1047
00:41:46,679 --> 00:41:47,400
talk about death

1048
00:41:48,639 --> 00:41:49,760
and keep bringing it up

1049
00:41:51,320 --> 00:41:52,400
deliberately provoking you

1050
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:54,719
making you angry

1051
00:41:55,039 --> 00:41:57,079
Can you at least tell me how I die?

1052
00:41:57,079 --> 00:41:58,559
What if I die from food safety issues?

1053
00:41:58,639 --> 00:41:59,960
I just want to know when I'll die

1054
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:01,960
You can coax him

1055
00:42:04,119 --> 00:42:05,079
or you can yell at him

1056
00:42:07,880 --> 00:42:09,159
But the one thing

1057
00:42:12,239 --> 00:42:14,000
is that you cannot cry with him

1058
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:20,599
Because he

1059
00:42:22,159 --> 00:42:24,000
is actually the one who is most afraid

1060
00:42:27,039 --> 00:42:28,800
If you cry in front of him

1061
00:42:31,480 --> 00:42:33,679
that resolve he's been holding on to

1062
00:42:35,719 --> 00:42:36,760
will dissipate

1063
00:42:39,239 --> 00:42:40,119
If it dissipates

1064
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:42,679
that resolve

1065
00:42:44,599 --> 00:42:46,079
can never be gathered again

1066
00:42:51,960 --> 00:42:52,760
So

1067
00:42:53,920 --> 00:42:55,000
so I cannot cry

1068
00:42:57,599 --> 00:42:58,599
I cannot fall apart

1069
00:43:00,719 --> 00:43:01,519
All of this

1070
00:43:03,239 --> 00:43:04,239
will come to an end

1071
00:43:08,039 --> 00:43:12,119
Madam, your eyeballs seem to be leaking water

1072
00:43:23,039 --> 00:43:23,559
Thank you.

1073
00:43:23,960 --> 00:43:25,039
Thank you all for your cooperation.

1074
00:43:27,119 --> 00:43:28,039
Thanks for your hard work.

1075
00:43:29,440 --> 00:43:30,880
Don't get too excited just yet.

1076
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:32,840
I've done what I promised you.

1077
00:43:32,920 --> 00:43:33,760
When will my mom quit?

1078
00:43:34,320 --> 00:43:34,920
Don't worry.

1079
00:43:36,239 --> 00:43:36,880
Monday.

1080
00:43:37,679 --> 00:43:39,280
It'll be your mom's last day.

1081
00:43:41,239 --> 00:43:44,239
It'll be your mom's last day at work.

1082
00:43:46,079 --> 00:43:47,239
Your hosting style...

1083
00:43:47,719 --> 00:43:48,920
Lay off those talk shows.

1084
00:43:52,079 --> 00:43:53,079
I learned all that from them.

1085
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:55,800
I'm so full. Stuffed.

1086
00:43:56,199 --> 00:43:58,159
Me too. My belly is huge.

1087
00:43:58,719 --> 00:43:59,400
Me too.

1088
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:00,960
That place was pretty good, though.

1089
00:44:02,239 --> 00:44:02,840
Let's go again next time.

1090
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:04,920
I don't want to go home. I don't want to sleep.

1091
00:44:05,320 --> 00:44:06,599
Shall we go to the next place?

1092
00:44:06,599 --> 00:44:07,679
Let's sit a while longer.

1093
00:44:08,039 --> 00:44:08,920
Let's not, Fang'er.

1094
00:44:08,920 --> 00:44:09,719
We're a bit tired.

1095
00:44:09,800 --> 00:44:11,599
Plus, Xi and I have to get up early tomorrow.

1096
00:44:11,599 --> 00:44:12,320
To pack and ship orders.

1097
00:44:13,159 --> 00:44:14,480
And I only have one day off.

1098
00:44:15,800 --> 00:44:16,280
Alright.

1099
00:44:17,039 --> 00:44:17,960
See you in class the day after tomorrow.

1100
00:44:18,639 --> 00:44:19,199
See you at school.

1101
00:44:19,880 --> 00:44:20,280
Bye.

1102
00:44:20,840 --> 00:44:21,519
Xiaocan's shoes.

1103
00:44:21,639 --> 00:44:22,119
Thanks.

1104
00:44:22,599 --> 00:44:23,119
You should head back.

1105
00:44:23,199 --> 00:44:24,480
Okay, we'll get going then.

1106
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:25,039
We're off, Fang'er.

1107
00:44:25,119 --> 00:44:25,679
Bye, bye.

1108
00:44:25,679 --> 00:44:26,360
Stay safe.

1109
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:27,159
Text me when you get there.

1110
00:44:27,840 --> 00:44:28,400
Bye.

1111
00:44:28,400 --> 00:44:28,840
Bye.

1112
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:45,840
But...

1113
00:44:47,519 --> 00:44:49,199
Domestic seeds sell by the pound.

1114
00:44:49,719 --> 00:44:51,480
Imported seeds sell by the grain.

1115
00:44:52,280 --> 00:44:54,400
Imported seeds have monopolized the market.

1116
00:44:55,119 --> 00:44:56,199
Our company takes the easy way out.

1117
00:44:56,599 --> 00:44:58,280
And gives domestic breeding no chance.

1118
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:00,000
Now...

1119
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:02,199
I've become an insider.

1120
00:45:02,840 --> 00:45:05,039
Sometimes I even have to block the door.

1121
00:45:05,800 --> 00:45:08,159
Fang'er, you really need to think this through.

1122
